  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We investigate the particle and kinetic-energy densities for $N$ non-interacting fermions confined in a given potential. Using Gutzwiller's semi-classical Green function, we describe the oscillating parts of the densities in terms of non-periodic classical orbits. We obtain simple analytical formulae for the density oscillations near the center (i.e. around the minimum) of a one-dimensional potential. We present similar formulae for arbitrary smooth potentials with spherical symmetry in arbitrary dimensions and universal relations between the oscillating parts of the kinetic and particle densities.</subfield>
